                  REUBEN 
                  GOOCH
               <interp inst="t18160529-78-person771" type="surname" value="GOOCH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160529-78-person771" type="given" value="REUBEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160529-78-person771" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was a <rs id="t18160529-78-viclabel426" type="occupation">sailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18160529-78-victim770 t18160529-78-viclabel426"></join>. I lost my watch on the 18th of May, between eight and nine o'clock at night. I fell in with the prisoner at the Crown and Thistle, by <placeName id="t18160529-78-crimeloc427">Tower-hill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18160529-78-crimeloc427" type="placeName" value="Tower-hill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18160529-78-crimeloc427" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18160529-78-off424 t18160529-78-crimeloc427"></join>; we had four or five pots of ale to drink. I was not half drunk; I was a little drunkish. I told him, I wanted a ship; he told me he could get me one, and asked me to take a walk to see the mate. The watch was safe in my pocket then; and we went out, and I felt him draw the watch out, and he ran off as quick as he could, and I ran after him; but he turned out of my sight, and I lost him. I am sure he is the man, I can swear positively.</p>
